root: ^Wow! How did you find that? Where do these stairs lead?
^I couldn't find the boat and decided to return. You probably forgot to tie it up and the tide swept it out to the sea. Can I go with you now?

^Ha, your silence means consent! Besides, now you can't let me go, because I might let the world know about your little find, and a bunch of archeologists will be here pretty soon with their shovels ready.
^Relax, I'm just kidding! You have no sense of humor whatsoever.
^Be careful with jokes; you might get misinterpreted.
^If I thought you was serious, I would make you silent. Forever.
^Oh, you’re joking now! You need to show some emotions so I could tell whether you’re being serious or not.
^I think you are my main problem right now…
^Are we going to keep arguing or shall we go down the stairs to see what is out there?
